<HEADLINE> Two Firefighters Die in Kentucky </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CRANSTON, Ky. (AP) -- Two volunteer firefighters were killed  
while battling a blaze in the Daniel Boone National Forest. 
</P>
<P>
	Kenneth Nickell, 28, and Kevin Smith, 30, were fighting one of  
27 wildfires reported Tuesday in Kentucky. Witnesses said the two 
men were overtaken by flames when the wind shifted. They died of 
smoke inhalation. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire burned 60 acres before being brought under control  
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
