<HEADLINE> Crane Collapses Into Va. River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- A crane operator was presumed dead after a  
concrete causeway collapsed, pitching his rig into the cold, murky 
Elizabeth River with him trapped inside. 
</P>
<P>
	Divers gave up the search for George Freeman of Eure, N.C., on  
Wednesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	Freeman, an employee of Norfolk Shipbuilding and Drydock Corp.,  
was driving the crane Tuesday night when a 60-to-80-foot section of 
the causeway gave way. 
</P>
<P>
	Four workers jumped into the water to try to rescue Freeman, but  
he disappeared from view. The water is up to 60 feet deep. 
</P>
