<DOCNO> APW19990407.0043 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 05:55:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> KLM, Alitalia Combine Sales Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) -- KLM Royal Dutch Airlines and  
Italy's national carrier, Alitalia SpA, are integrating their sales 
offices in Italy and the Benelux countries as part of their 
long-term alliance. 
</P>
<P>
	As of Tuesday, Alitalia's sales organizations in the Netherlands  
were fully integrated into KLM Benelux, meaning KLM Benelux sales 
staff will handle commercial matters presented by Alitalia 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
	As of May 1, KLM's sales operations in Italy will be under  
Alitalia's wing, the companies said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In November, KLM and Alitalia signed a cooperation agreement  
which also includes cargo and passenger joint ventures. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
