<HEADLINE> Olympic Committee Honors Battelle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. (AP) -- Freestyle skier Ann Battelle was  
selected Female Athlete of the Month for the second month in a row 
by the U.S. Olympic Committee on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Battelle won the moguls competition at the Freestyle World  
Championships in Switzerland, and took the bronze medal in the dual 
moguls. 
</P>
<P>
	Archer James Butts was voted Male Athlete of the Month after  
breaking the American record in the compound bow division at the 
National Indoor Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	The Team of the Month award went to the relay team of Andre  
Morris, Dameon Johnson, Deon Minor and Milton Campbell. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4x400 team set a world record at the World Indoor  
Championships. 
