<HEADLINE> Company Recalls Eggrolls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Los Angeles-based Fil-Am Specialty Foods is  
recalling two flavors of A I Tropical-brand Philippine-style 
eggrolls because the wrappers do not list eggs as an ingredient. 
</P>
<P>
	People with allergies to eggs run the risk of serious or  
life-threatening reactions if they consume the products, and should 
return them to the place of purchase for a refund. 
</P>
<P>
	The eggs rolls are sold in 24-ounce bags bearing the production  
code ``0009228-0002089,'' and labeled as distributed by Phil. 
Foodtrade Corp., and Foodasia International. They come in the 
flavors ``vegetable lumpia (plain)'' and ``lumpia vegetable with 
shrimp.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
