<HEADLINE> Yes It's True Wins Lafayette Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Yes It's True took the lead at the gate  
and pulled away to a five-length victory in the $107,000 Lafayette 
Stakes at Keeneland on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Yes It's True, a son of 1988 Breeders' Cup Juvenile winner Is It  
True, broke quickly from the second post position and settled near 
the rail. Fantastic Finish pulled to within a head a few strides 
later, but Yes It's True took control midway through the turn. 
</P>
<P>
	The colt covered seven furlongs in 1:22 and paid $2.40 and  
$2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Trickey Crew rallied to finish five lengths behind in second and  
returned $2.10. Fort La Roca was another 1 1/2 lengths behind in 
third. 
</P>
<P>
	Yes It's True is expected to run next in the Derby Trial, the  
opening day stake of the upcoming Churchill Downs meet. 
</P>
