<HEADLINE> Plane Diverted From Fla. to Boston </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- A plane flying from London to Florida touched down  
in Boston on Wednesday when the crew found a suspicious package. An 
X-ray later showed that it contained a cellular phone. 
</P>
<P>
	The Virgin Atlantic 747 was about 300 miles from Boston when the  
package was found under a seat, said Tom Kinton, Logan 
International Airport's director of aviation. It was ``deemed 
suspicious because nobody could claim it,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The plane, with 485 passengers and crew, landed in Boston around  
2:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	The passengers and crew were placed on shuttle buses on the  
tarmac while authorities investigated. The plane and passengers 
continued their journey to Orlando, Fla., after refueling around 
5:30 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
