<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Staples Opens 15 24-hour Chains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- In this global economy, business doesn't sleep.  
</P>
<P>
	Seeking to capitalize on that notion, Staples is opening 15 of  
its office-supply stores around the clock. 
</P>
<P>
	The move puts Staples into direct competition with 24-hour  
chains such as Kinko's, which are popular among business travelers 
and students needing photocopies, laser printouts, or access to a 
computer and the Internet at any time day or night. 
</P>
<P>
	But Staples also hopes to draw customers who need three-ring  
binders and fancy highlighting for projects due the next morning as 
well as those who don't have time to shop during the day. 
</P>
<P>
	``With today's hectic pace, sometimes the only opportunity to  
shop for office supplies is in the off hours,'' Staples president 
Jim Peters said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 15 all-night stores are opening in areas near colleges or in  
dense urban communities in nine states: California, Indiana, 
Massachusetts, Michigan, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, 
Pennsylvania and Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
	Staples executives said there were no immediate plans to extend  
the 24-hour openings across the 950-store chain. 
</P>
<P>
	Four stores -- two in the Boston area, one in West Los Angeles  
and one in Springfield, Penn. -- were tested with the 24-hour 
concept before the chain broadened to 15 stores, said Christina 
Erridge, a store spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
	Most stores in the chain now open at 7 a.m. and close at 9 p.m.  
or 11 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	Staples, based in Westboro, Mass., is believed to be the first  
among the office superstores to open all night, analysts said. 
</P>
<P>
	Karen Sack, an analyst with the S&AMP;P Equity Group in New York,  
said the hour expansion made sense but may not necessarily add to 
the bottom line. ``I wouldn't raise earnings estimates based on the 
fact that they're going to do it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When other industries such as supermarkets began opening all  
night, competitors quickly followed. The same is likely to happen 
with Staples, Sack said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Once one starts, then almost everybody has to do it at some  
point because it's the name that remains in the consumer's mind and 
attracts people -- whether they're there at midnight or not,'' she 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 15 all-night Staples stores are located in: Alhambra,  
Calif.; Studio City, Calif.; West Los Angeles, Calif.; Bloomington, 
Ind.; Boston's Brighton neighborhood; Danvers, Mass.; Framingham, 
Mass.; Tysons Corner, Va.; East Lansing, Mich.; Fayetteville, N.C.; 
New York, N.Y.; Yonkers, N.Y.; Springfield, N.J.; Springfield, 
Penn.; Bryn Mawr, Penn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
