<HEADLINE> IRS Tax Filing Statistics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Selected figures from this year's tax filing season through 	
April 2 in comparison with the same period last year: 
</P>
<P>
                           *Returns Filed 	
</P>
<P>
	--69.6 million, up 3.3 percent. 	
</P>
<P>
                         *Electronic filing 	
</P>
<P>
	--Total, 24.9 million, up 16.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Computer, 20.1 million, up 23.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Telephone, 4.8 million, down 5.6 percent. 	
</P>
<P>
                             *Refunds 	
</P>
<P>
	--54.8 million, up 4.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Total: $86.4 billion, up 19.8 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Average: $1,575, up 15 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Direct deposit: $18.9 million, up 18.2 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
