<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 10:45:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Entertainment Highlights in History  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Entertainment highlights during the week of April 11-17:  
</P>
<P>
	60 years ago: ``Wuthering Heights'' starred Merle Oberon and  
Laurence Olivier. The film was directed by William Wyler. 
</P>
<P>
	55 years ago: William Wyler's ``The Memphis Belle'' opened in  
Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
	45 years ago: Bill Haley and His Comets recorded ``Rock Around  
the Clock'' for Decca Records. 
</P>
<P>
	35 years ago: ``Tom Jones'' won Oscars for best picture and best  
director. Sidney Poitier won an Oscar for his role as a handyman in 
``Lilies of the Field.'' 
</P>
<P>
	And the Rolling Stones' self-titled debut album was released in  
Britain. Two weeks later, it had broken the album chart 
stranglehold by The Beatles, which had lasted 51 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	30 years ago: ``Oliver!'' won six Oscars, including best picture  
and best director. 
</P>
<P>
	25 years ago: The Who's Pete Townshend made his solo debut at a  
concert in London, accompanied only by homemade tapes. 
</P>
<P>
	10 years ago: ``Loc-ed After Dark,'' an album by rapper Tone  
Loc, topped the U.S. album chart. 
</P>
<P>
	Singer Anita Baker captured three awards for her single and  
album, ``Giving You the Best That I Got,'' at the third annual Soul 
Train Music Awards. Michael Jackson was honored for his hit ``Man 
in the Mirror.'' 
</P>
<P>
	And entertainer Jack Jones received a star on the Hollywood Walk  
of Fame. Jones' star was placed beside one honoring his father, 
actor-singer Allan Jones. 
</P>
<P>
	One year ago: Meryl Streep was the first-ever recipient of the  
Bette Davis Lifetime Achievement Award. The award recognizes an 
actress whose career ``distinctly parallels the high professional 
standards set by Bette Davis.'' 
</P>
<P>
	And the Palm Beach International Film Festival honored  
51-year-old Sylvester Stallone for lifetime achievement. 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken 10 years ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``It's the first time in my life that I have memorized words  
written by a genius and I'm working with people who know their 
stuff.'' -- Actor Dustin Hoffman, rehearsing his part as Shylock in 
a London production of ``The Merchant of Venice.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken one year ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``Hip-hop gives me the freedom that movies will never give me.  
With movies you've got so many suits putting their two cents in.'' 
-- Rapper-actor Ice Cube. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
