<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 10:33:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Prince Andrew Adds Online Pages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Prince Andrew on Wednesday launched an addition to  
the royal family's website that gives further glimpses of their 
lifestyle, including their charity work and their art collections. 
</P>
<P>
	Andrew, an experienced Internet user, officially put the  
magazine-style pages -- called Royal Insight -- online at a 
cyber-cafe near Buckingham Palace. 
</P>
<P>
	In contrast to the main site, which comprises mostly reference  
material, Royal Insight will focus on the day-to-day activities of 
members of the royal family, with an emphasis on photographic 
material. 
</P>
<P>
	Main elements include coverage of recent royal engagements and  
texts of royal speeches; ``Gallery Online,'' showing the works of 
the Royal Collection of artworks; features written by family 
members about their favorite causes and an interactive 
question-and-answer section. 
</P>
<P>
	A new issue of the magazine will come online on the third day of  
each month. 
</P>
<P>
	Since Queen Elizabeth II launched the royal website in March  
1997, it has averaged 3-4 million ``hits'' a week from around the 
world. 
</P>
<P>
	---------	 
</P>
<P>
	The royal website is at www.royal.gov.uk. The new section can be  
found at www.royalinsight.gov.uk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
