<HEADLINE> Champions Cup Soccer Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- A pair of last-minute goals left both semifinals  
of the European Champions Cup tied after Wednesday's first legs. 
</P>
<P>
	Manchester United, leading the English Premier league, managed a  
1-1 draw at home against Juventus on a goal by Ryan Giggs in injury 
time. 
</P>
<P>
	And in Kiev, Bayern Munich came away with a 3-3 draw with Dynamo  
on Carsten Janker's score in the closing seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite failing to secure a victory, the point at Old Trafford  
may have been enough to assure Juventus of a fourth consecutive 
appearance in the Champions Cup final. 
</P>
<P>
	The Italian champions silenced 55,000 Manchester fans when  
Antonio Conte scored in the 25th minute on a play sparked by French 
World Cup hero Zinedine Zidane. 
</P>
<P>
	Juve looked set to return home to Turin with a first-leg lead  
and set up yet another final, this time in Barcelona May 27. 
</P>
<P>
	But United hit back strongly in the late stages and Giggs scored  
the equalizer in injury time after Juve failed to clear a 
right-wing cross from David Beckham. 
</P>
<P>
	It was a similar story in Kiev.  
</P>
<P>
	Dynamo's Andrii Shevchenko, who scored three times in  
quarterfinal games against defending titlist Real Madrid, hit the 
first goal and created the second for Kakha Kaladze with his free 
kick two minutes before halftime. 
</P>
<P>
	Seconds before the half, Michael Tarnat's 30-yard free kick  
bounced past Kiev goalkeeper Olexander Shovkovsky for Bayern, but 
Vitaly Kossovskyi made it 3-1 five minutes into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
	Steffan Effenberg's 78th minute free kick brought it back to 3-2  
and, in the final minute, Janker hit the Bayern equalizer from 
close range. 
</P>
</TEXT>
