<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> DuPont Allies With Health Web Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) -- DuPont Co. is entering an alliance with  
WebMD Inc., an Internet site, as part of its plan to improve its 
life sciences business, the company announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	WebMD will make DuPont the exclusive provider of information on  
its subscription physician service and free consumer site about 
prescription drugs, over-the-counter medicines, nutritional 
supplements and medical foods. 
</P>
<P>
	DuPont has agreed to underwrite six million months of  
subscriptions to the site for doctors. In exchange, WebMD will 
promote DuPont's life sciences offerings online, as well as through 
broadcast and print outlets. DuPont valued the alliance at $220 
million. 
</P>
<P>
	WebMD was started in October 1998 and offers Internet services  
for physicians, including a medical library, insurance verification 
and referral authorizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
