<HEADLINE> Stock Prices Mixed; Dow Up 61.05 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Prices were mixed on Wall Street today as  
investors rewarded companies reporting strong first-quarter 
earnings but shied away from technology stocks. 
</P>
<P>
	At 3 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
up 61.05 at 10,024.54. Broader stock indicators were mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks opened strongly as aluminum maker Alcoa released  
first-quarter earnings that soundly beat analysts' expectations. 
The good news from Alcoa, a component of the Dow, helped many 
blue-chips move higher. Alcoa itself was up 2 7/8 to 43 15/16. 
</P>
<P>
	AT&AMP;T, another Dow stock, was up 4 1/4 at 84 3/8.  
</P>
<P>
	The financial sector was mostly higher as analysts said banks  
and brokerages have hinted they will report strong earnings when 
they begin releasing first-quarter results next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Ned Riley, chief investment officer at BankBoston, said  
investors may be rewarding those companies for weathering the 
global financial crises of 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Chase Manhattan rose 4 7/8 to 84 1/8, and Merrill Lynch rose 4 1/2 to  
95 5/8. 
</P>
<P>
	But computer companies held the market in check after Merrill  
Lynch analysts warned of some tough times ahead for the high-tech 
sector. 
</P>
<P>
	The problem, according to William Meehan, chief market analyst  
at Cantor Fitzgerald, is that stocks are too overvalued to 
withstand even the slightest hint of caution. ``It doesn't take 
much to trigger any kind of stampede,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Software maker Novell slipped 1 3/16 to 22 7/8, and Sun  
Microsystems fell 2 1/4 to 138 3/8. 
</P>
<P>
	Still, traders were optimistically looking ahead to an  
after-hours earnings release from Yahoo!, which was expected to 
beat analyst estimates. Yahoo! rose 11/16 to 215 9/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Revlon rose 3 3/8 to 23 3/8 after the cosmetics maker said it is  
considering the sale of one or more of its businesses. 
</P>
<P>
	The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 5.06 at 1,322.95, and the  
Nasdaq composite index, which is heavily weighted with technology 
stocks, was down 11.27 at 2,551.90. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues were ahead of advancers by an 11-to-9 margin on  
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 642.4 million 
shares, ahead of Tuesday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was up 1.79 at 614.11, and the American  
Stock Exchange composite index was up 3.36 at 718.57. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
