<HEADLINE> British Airways To Fly to Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- British Airways plans to start flying to Libya now  
that the United Nations has suspended sanctions against that 
country, which on Monday handed over two Libyans suspected of 
blowing up a Pan Am jet over Lockerbie, Scotland, in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
	The flights between London and Tripoli, the Libyan capital, are  
to begin later this month. 
</P>
<P>
	The airline, which has never flown to the Libyan capital before,  
said Wednesday it plans three flights a week using Boeing 737 
aircraft. 
</P>
<P>
	After years of haggling, Libya agreed to surrendered the  
suspected terrorists for trial in the Netherlands under Scottish 
law. 

