<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cardinals: Vina Deal Is Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Middle reliever Manny Aybar and a minor league  
pitcher for Brewers All-Star second baseman Fernando Vina sounds 
like a pretty good deal for the St. Louis Cardinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Not to general manager Walt Jocketty, who says the Cardinals are  
just as strapped for pitchers as the team that wants to take Aybar 
off their hands. Thus, that deal likely won't happen. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't sacrifice any more pitching,'' Jocketty said. ``If you  
do that, then you open another hole. Right now, anything we do is 
going to be for pitching.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Cardinals' winter game plan had been to acquire a No. 1  
starter and quality shortstop and then fill in at second base with 
a lesser talent such as Polanco, David Howard or Pat Kelly, who was 
the final roster cut. They got the shortstop they wanted in Edgar 
Renteria, but not the No. 1 pitcher, yet the fill-in plan at second 
remains. 
</P>
<P>
	Aybar, 24, hasn't done much at the major-league but remains a  
hot property for the Cardinals. He was 10-0 at Triple-A Memphis and 
6-6 with a 5.98 ERA with St. Louis, including 14 starts, and was 
guaranteed a roster spot because he's out of options. 
</P>
<P>
	Jocketty is hopeful a combination of Polanco and Howard, who is  
on the 15-day disabled list with an injured groin, can be 
effective. 
</P>
<P>
	``Polanco, I think, will surprise some people if he gets a  
chance to play enough,'' Jocketty said. ``He can do a lot of little 
things and he takes a great at-bat up there all the time. Howard 
gives us great defense and is a switch-hitter.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Polanco, 23, batted .254 with one homer and 11 RBIs in 114  
at-bats last season. Howard, 32, missed the second half of the 
season with a shoulder injury and batted .245 with two homers and 
12 RBIs in 102 at-bats. 
</P>
<P>
	Howard injured his groin in the final inning of the final spring  
game on Saturday. He said Wednesday he could play, but the 
Cardinals couldn't afford to risk keeping him on the roster since 
Renteria is getting limited duty from a bone bruise that kept him 
out all spring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
