<HEADLINE> Boston Winner Hits $197M Jackpot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- There was just one winning ticket in the six-state  
Big Game's record $197 million jackpot, and it was sold in Boston, 
lottery officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
	The ticket -- bearing the winning numbers drawn Tuesday of 12,  
17, 22, 33 and 44, with the Big Money Ball of 25 -- was sold at a 
Star Market supermarket near Fenway Park, lottery officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	No one had come forward to claim the prize as of late morning.  
</P>
<P>
	``We're all thrilled,'' said Linda Marino, a Star Market  
employee. ``It's just pure excitement here. Now we're waiting to 
see who won the money. Hopefully, an employee.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The store will get $50,000 for selling the winning ticket.  
</P>
<P>
	The jackpot had been growing since Feb. 2. The jackpot had been  
estimated at $190 million Tuesday night, but the final flood of 
ticket sales raised it by $7 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The Big Game is played in Georgia, Illinois, Maryland,  
Massachusetts, Michigan and Virginia, and the drawing is held in 
Georgia. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. record for a lottery prize is the $295.7 million  
jackpot last July in the Powerball lottery, played in 20 states and 
the District of Columbia. It was shared by 13 workers at an Ohio 
machine shop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
