<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed today in European trading  
with major currencies. Gold prices were higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar rose to 121.36 Japanese yen from 120.98 yen late  
Tuesday, but was lower against the euro, which rose to $1.0795 from 
$1.0728. 
</P>
<P>
	Other late European dollar rates compared with late Tuesday  
included 1.4781 Swiss francs, down from 1.4874, and 1.5036 Canadian 
dollars, up from 1.5007. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5949, down from $1.5992.  
</P>
<P>
	In New York at midday, the dollar was worth 121.28 yen, 1.4805  
Swiss francs and 1,5008 Canadian dollars. The euro was worth 
$1.0789 and the British pound was worth $1.5973. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on 
Wednesday's euro rates, the dollar is worth: 1.8118 German marks, 
down from 1.8231; 6.0765 French francs, down from 6.1144; and 
1,793.67 Italian lire, down from 1,804.88. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $280.10 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$278.60 on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $280.10, up from $278.40.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed at 280.45 in Hong Kong, unchanged from late Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $4.97 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$4.96. 
