<HEADLINE> Brazil 7, United States 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) -- Brazil, led by strikers Fabio Junior and  
Denilson, routed the United States 7-0 in a under-23 game 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. team, missing several players who are with Major League  
Soccer teams, spent most of the game trying vainly to keep up with 
their tricky, fitter-looking opponents. 
</P>
<P>
	Two slipups by U.S. goalie Matt Napoleon in the first half gave  
Brazil a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	He brought down Fabio Junior, of Italy's AC Roma, in the penalty  
box after 23 minutes. Denilson, of Spain's Betis, swept in the 
penalty kick. 
</P>
<P>
	Then, 12 minutes later, Napoleon failed to hold a curling free  
kick and Marcos Paulo pounced on it to score. 
</P>
<P>
	As the U.S. team started to tire in the second half, an unmarked  
Warley steered a header into the net for Brazil at 60 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Six minutes later, substitute Roni scored his first goal for the  
national team. He added his second 12 minutes later, driving a 
left-footed shot home. 
</P>
<P>
	Arujo chipped a ball over Napoleon as the keeper came off his  
line for the sixth goal. Rodrigo made it seven right at the end 
with a penalty kick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
