<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Teens Plead Guilty in Nev. Deaths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BATTLE MOUNTAIN, Nev. (AP) -- A teen-age boy who said his mom  
made him mad because she wouldn't let him ``do stuff'' and a friend 
pleaded guilty Wednesday to killing the boy's family. 
</P>
<P>
	Kyle Ray and Colby Becker plotted the killings and traded off  
pulling the trigger, killing Ray's parents and 12-year-old sister 
in June, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	Charged as adults, Ray pleaded guilty to two counts of murder  
with use of a deadly weapon and Becker pleaded guilty to one count 
of the same charge. 
</P>
<P>
	The boys were both 15 at the time of the killings in this mining  
town about 220 miles east of Reno. They face up to life in prison 
with or without the possibility of parole when they are sentenced 
in June. 
</P>
<P>
	They are too young for the death penalty.  
</P>
<P>
	When Ray and Becker entered their pleas in district court and  
were asked by the judge to tell him what happened, ``Becker said 'I 
shot Kyle's dad in the back of the head,''' prosecutor Robert Estes 
said. ``And Kyle Ray said 'I shot my mom and my sister.''' 
</P>
<P>
	``Ever since I got this case I've been looking for a reason and  
there isn't one,'' said prosecutor Robert Estes said. 
</P>
<P>
	The best explanation he could find was a statement Ray made to  
police about how his mom made him mad because ``she wouldn't let me 
do stuff,'' Estes said. 
</P>
<P>
	In exchange for their pleas, Estes said he will not oppose the  
chance for parole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
