<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, American Stock 
Exchange and Nasdaq Stock Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Seagram Co., up 2 5/16 to 57 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Universal Music, a unit of Seagram, and BMG Entertainment, a  
unit of Bertelsmann AG, will merge their Internet music operations, 
creating a large Web destination to sell compact disks and promote 
recording artists. 

</P>
<P>
 *Ford Motor Co., up 2 5/16 at 60 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	March was a record-breaking month for the auto giant, as pickups  
and sport utility vehicles attracted thousands more buyers to Ford 
dealerships. The company announced Tuesday it is increasing 
production. 

</P>
<P>
 *Watson Pharmaceuticals Inc., up 4 1/8 at 46 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Corona, Calif., drug maker will be added to the Standard &AMP;  
Poor's 500 index. Stocks added to the index generally get at least 
a short-term boost, because index fund managers must buy the stock 
to ensure their funds' performance mirrors the index. 

</P>
<P>
 *Micron Technology, down 2 15/16 at 50 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Micron fell along with a number of semiconductor makers after  
Merrill Lynch forecast a tough future for a wide range of 
high-technology companies. 

</P>
<P>
                               *AMEX    	

</P>
<P>
 *Cognitronics, up 1 5/8 at 12 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Lucent Technologies Inc. signed an agreement to purchase and  
resell Cognitronics' McIAS 16xx product. Cognitronics makes 
telecommunications products like voice mail and telephone 
announcement systems. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Network Associates, down 5 5/16 at 16 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Santa Clara, Calif., company said late Tuesday it expects  
first-quarter operating earnings of 30 cents to 32 cents a share. 
Analysts surveyed by First Call Corp. have estimated earnings of 48 
cents a share. Several analysts downgraded their outlook on the 
stock this morning. 

</P>
<P>
 *Spyglass Inc., up 6 at 14 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Spyglass, a developer of Internet technologies, has entered a  
new technology licensing and service agreement with Microsoft, 
which it expects to provide it with at least $20 million in revenue 
over a three-year period. 

</P>
<P>
 *Engineering Animation, down 20 3/16 at 19 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The Ames, Iowa, provider of design and animation software said  
that it expects its first-quarter earnings to come in 15 percent 
below analysts' estimates of 26 cents a share. 

</P>
<P>
 *FVC.com Inc., down 10 3/8 at 7    	
</P>
<P>
	The software maker said it expects to lose 20 cents to 22 cents  
a share in the first quarter, compared with First Call Corp.'s 
estimate of profits of 3 cents a share. FVC.com said it has been 
hurt by substantially lighter orders from Bay Networks, once a 
major customer. 

</P>
</TEXT>
