<HEADLINE> Suns Activate Rex Chapman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The Phoenix Suns activated Rex Chapman from the  
injured list Wednesday and released guard Jimmy Oliver early from 
his 10-day contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Chapman missed five games because of turf toe on his left foot.  
He has struggled this season, averaging 12.3 points per game. 
</P>
<P>
	Oliver played 11 minutes in two games for the Suns. He made one  
basket, a 3-pointer, in three attempts. 
</P>
<P>
	The Suns also activated guard Marko Milic and placed guard Toby  
Bailey on the injured list. 
</P>
<P>
	Milic was placed on the injured list March 2 with tendinitis in  
his right knee. 
</P>
<P>
	The Suns said Bailey also had tendinitis in his right knee.  
</P>
<P>
	Bailey also was on the injured list from Feb. 19 to March 2 with  
tendinitis in the knee. Bailey has played in 21 games, including 
nine starts, and has averaged 2.7 points and 2.3 rebounds per game. 
</P>
