<HEADLINE> Cabrera Named To AP Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Denise Cabrera, Washington metro editor for  
The Associated Press since 1993, has been appointed news editor for 
assignments in the AP's Washington bureau. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Chief of Bureau Sandy  
Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	Cabrera joined the AP in 1987, working as an editor and reporter  
on the metropolitan and national desks in the Washington bureau. 
She became supervisor of the Metro report in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
	Cabrera, 46, is from New York City and is a graduate of Adelphi  
University. Before joining the AP, she worked for NBC News in 
Washington and for The Washington Times. 
