<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Andy Garcia  
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Andy Garcia was born April 12, 1956, in  
Havana, Cuba. His father was a prominent lawyer and his mother 
taught English. The family left Cuba when he was 5 and settled in 
Miami Beach, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
	Garcia liked movies as a child but felt no special desire to act  
until he went to Florida International University. After college, 
he moved to Los Angeles, hoping to break into movies. First came a 
spot in the TV pilot for ``Hill Street Blues.'' Theater work 
followed, with appearances in ``Anastasia,'' ``The Cherry 
Orchard,'' ``Don't Trust Life'' and other works. 
</P>
<P>
	Movies began in 1983 with ``Blue Skies Again'' and ``A Night in  
Heaven.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Agents wanted him to abandon his Latin roots.  
</P>
<P>
	``Change my name, yeah, that was an immediate suggestion by  
early agents I was attempting to get,'' he said. ``They said 
`change your name, fix your nose, cut your hair, lift some weights' 
-- stuff like that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Garcia refused.  
</P>
<P>
	 *Breakthrough:* Garcia hit the big time playing sidekick to  
mob-busters Kevin Costner and Sean Connery in ``The Untouchables'' 
(1987) and then three years later in Francis Ford Coppola's ``The 
Godfather: Part III.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Garcia became a top draw. He was often cast either as a cop or  
as a hood. 
</P>
<P>
	He and Meg Ryan were co-stars in ``When a Man Loves a Woman.''  
He then worked in quirkier films like ``Things to Do in Denver When 
You're Dead'' and ``The Disappearance of Garcia Lorca,'' about the 
famed Spanish poet. 
</P>
<P>
	Currently, Garcia stars opposite Andie MacDowell in ``Just the  
Ticket.'' Garcia was a producer for the movie, which was 10 years 
in the making, and also wrote songs for the film's Latin-influenced 
soundtrack. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``There's nothing that I cherish more than my culture  
and what I am. But to call me the great Hispanic actor is 
ridiculous; it's racism. They don't call Dustin Hoffman the great 
Jewish-American actor.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays April 11-17:  
</P>
<P>
	April 11: Actor Joel Grey is 67. Actor Peter Riegart is 52.  
Actor Bill Irwin is 49. Singer Lisa Stansfield is 33. Musician 
Dylan Keefe of Marcy Playground is 29. 
</P>
<P>
	April 12: Actor Ed O'Neill is 53. Talk-show host David Letterman  
is 52. Singer-actor David Cassidy is 49. Actor Andy Garcia is 43. 
Country singer Vince Gill is 42. Musician Will Sergeant of Echo and 
the Bunnymen is 41. Singer Amy Ray of the Indigo Girls is 35. 
Actress Shannen Doherty is 28. Actress Claire Danes is 20. 
</P>
<P>
	April 13: Actor Paul Sorvino is 60. Singer Al Green is 53. Actor  
Ron Perlman is 49. Singer Peabo Bryson is 48. Musician Jimmy Destri 
of Blondie is 45. Musician Joey Mazzola of Sponge is 38. Actor Rick 
Schroder is 29. 
</P>
<P>
	April 14: Actor Rod Steiger is 74. Country singer Loretta Lynn  
is 64. Actress Julie Christie is 59. Actor Brad Garrett 
(``Everybody Loves Raymond'') is 39. Actor Anthony Michael Hall is 
31. Rapper DaBrat is 25. Actress Sarah Michelle Gellar is 22. 
</P>
<P>
	April 15: Country singer Roy Clark is 66. Actor Michael Tucci  
(``Diagnosis Murder'') is 49. Actress Emma Thompson is 40. Singer 
Samantha Fox is 33. Musician Ed O'Brien of Radiohead is 31. 
</P>
<P>
	April 16: Singer Bobby Vinton is 64. Actress Ellen Barkin is 45.  
Singer David Pirner of Soul Asylum is 35. Actor-comedian Martin 
Lawrence is 34. Actor Jon Cryer is 34. Actor Lukas Haas is 23. 
</P>
<P>
	April 17: Rock promoter Don Kirshner is 65. Singer-musician Pete  
Shelley of the Buzzcocks is 44. Singer Liz Phair is 32. 
</P>
