<HEADLINE> Quayle To Announce Run April 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUNTINGTON, Ind. (AP) -- Former Vice President Dan Quayle will  
formally announce his candidacy for the Republican presidential 
nomination at a political rally next week at his hometown high 
school, his campaign committee announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Quayle, 52, will be joined on stage at Huntington North High  
School, where he graduated in 1965, by his wife, Marilyn, and 
numerous state and national elected officials, his campaign said. 
</P>
<P>
	Quayle was George Bush's vice president and running mate in 1988  
and 1992. He moved from Indiana to Arizona in 1996. He formed an 
exploratory committee in February to begin raising campaign funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
