<HEADLINE> Marchment Suspended for Remark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Bryan Marchment's mouth got him in trouble and  
gave the San Jose Sharks' defenseman an unwanted night off. 
</P>
<P>
	Marchment sat out Tuesday night's 1-0 victory over Phoenix under  
an NHL suspension for an offensive remark directed at a member of 
the Vancouver Canucks. 
</P>
<P>
	During the second period of a 5-2 victory over the Canucks on  
Saturday in San Jose, Marchment called Donald Brashear, who is 
black, a ``big monkey.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Mr. Marchment has admitted making the remark,'' NHL hockey  
operations director Colin Campbell said. ``While we accept that 
there was no inappropriate intent on Mr. Marchment's part, we 
cannot excuse the conduct.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Marchment has been quoted as saying he uses ``big monkey'' to  
describe a bruising, physical player, such as Brashear, who is 
6-feet-2 and weighs 225 pounds. 
</P>
