<HEADLINE> Hamed Hires Steward as Boxing Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MANCHESTER, England (AP) -- Emanuel Steward, one of boxing's most  
respected trainers, has been hired as a corner coach by Prince 
Naseem Hamed for his fight Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Hamad will be defending his WBO featherweight title against Paul  
Ingle in Manchester. 
</P>
<P>
	Steward, who has trained WBC heavyweight champion Lennox Lewis  
and 26 other world champions, agreed to be in Hamed's corner for 
his 12th title defense after being asked by Hamed's brother and 
manager Raith Hamed. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought it would be a good idea to ask Manny, who is the  
best in the world at what he does, if he would work with Naz,'' 
Raith Hamed told the tabloid Sun newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
	Steward is in England with Thomas ``Hit Man'' Hearns, who is  
fighting fellow American Nate Millar in a cruiserweight bout on the 
undercard. 
</P>
<P>
	Steward will work with Hamed's new trainer Oscar Suarez.  
</P>
<P>
	Saurez is taking charge of his first bout for Hamed since the  
undefeated Briton's acrimonious split with long-time promoter Frank 
Warren. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is possible Manny will be involved with us in the future  
but we are not going to talk about that until after the fight,'' 
Raith Hamed said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ingles' manager, Frank Maloney, who also manages Lewis, said  
Hamed's hiring Steward was a ``gimmick.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``If Hamed really was serious about having Steward in his corner  
he would have hired him from day one,'' Maloney said Wednesday. 
</P>
